  "desc": "nchanter's Tools.\n\nThese special tools include the items you need to enchant weapons, armor, and other nonmagical items.\n\nComponents. Enchanter's tools include magical ink and paints, 6 sheets of parchment, a pen, a brush, a small hammer and chisel, mortal and pestle, several small glass vials, and a notebook with some basic enchantment recipes.\n\nArcana. Proficiency with Enchanter's tools allows grants you knowledge about magical theory. This knowledge aids you when making arcana checks related to the identification of magic items.\n\nInvestigation. Your knowledge of enchantment aids you when trying to identify magical traps. You are familiar with runes and other magical symbols and can more easily identify the mechanism of a magical trap.\n\nEnchanting. Enchanter's tools allow you to take magical items and imbue them with magic. (e.g take a nonmagical shortsword and imbue it into a +1 Shortsword).\n\n\nIdentify Curses. Your knowledge of enchanting gives you special insight when it comes to magical items. Over the course of a short rest, you can spend your time investigating a magical item to identify 1 curse or negative effect attached to an item. You must be in contact with the item to identify its curse. Spending more time investigating the item can reveal more detailed information regarding the objects' nature and the enchantments it has on it.\n\nActivity:\nIdentify the rarity of a magical item. DC 10\nIdentify a feature or function of a magic item. DC 15."
}